## 2026-04-03 - PreviewPanel Buttons/Forms/Card templates are static CSS demos that don't reflect the user's actual tokens
- Added `pickTokenByPatterns` helper and `resolvePreviewSlots` function that scan `allTokensFlat` to intelligently map user tokens to semantic UI roles (primary color, text, surface, border, error, spacing, border-radius, font-size) using pattern matching. Injects results as `--preview-*` CSS custom properties into the wrapper div alongside `cssVars`.
- Updated `ButtonsTemplate`, `FormsTemplate`, and `CardTemplate` to reference `--preview-*` vars as the first entry in their CSS var chains, keeping the existing hardcoded fallback chains intact. This means: if the user's tokens are detected, they're used; if not, the templates fall back gracefully to generic defaults.
- Detection heuristics cover common naming conventions: `primary`/`brand`/`accent` for primary color; `surface`/`background`/`canvas` for surface; `border`/`divider`/`separator` for border; `error`/`danger`/`destructive` for error state; spacing tokens sorted by value with percentile selection; border-radius tokens sorted by value; font-size tokens sorted by value.

